---
import PolicyLayout from '../../layouts/PolicyLayout.astro';
---

<PolicyLayout
  title="Admissions Policy | ISJ Jakarta"
  description="ISJ's Admissions Policy sets out how places are allocated, the application process, English language and SEND requirements, and financial obligations for enrolled families."
  policyName="Admissions Policy"
  lastReviewed="April 2026"
  category="Admissions and Operations"
  canonicalUrl="/policies/admissions"
>

  <!-- Policy metadata -->
  <div class="policy-meta mb-14" style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--charcoal-muted); line-height: 1.6;">
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; padding: 0.2rem 0;"><span style="min-width: 140px; flex-shrink: 0; color: var(--navy); opacity: 0.5;">Author</span><span>Academic Director, April 2026</span></div>
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; padding: 0.2rem 0;"><span style="min-width: 140px; flex-shrink: 0; color: var(--navy); opacity: 0.5;">Reviewed by</span><span>Board, April 2026</span></div>
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; padding: 0.2rem 0;"><span style="min-width: 140px; flex-shrink: 0; color: var(--navy); opacity: 0.5;">Approved by</span><span>SLT</span></div>
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; padding: 0.2rem 0;"><span style="min-width: 140px; flex-shrink: 0; color: var(--navy); opacity: 0.5;">Adopted by Board</span><span>April 2026</span></div>
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; padding: 0.2rem 0;"><span style="min-width: 140px; flex-shrink: 0; color: var(--navy); opacity: 0.5;">Next review</span><span>Academic Director, April 2027</span></div>
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; padding: 0.2rem 0;"><span style="min-width: 140px; flex-shrink: 0; color: var(--navy); opacity: 0.5;">Regulatory compliance</span><span>Independent School Standards Regulations (2014), Ministry of Education and Culture Requirements, COBIS Guidance</span></div>
  </div>

  <!-- Contents -->
  <nav class="mb-12" style="font-size: 13px; font-family: var(--font-body);">
    <p class="font-semibold text-navy mb-3" style="font-size: 13px; letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase;">Contents</p>
    <ol class="space-y-1" style="list-style: decimal; padding-left: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-charcoal-muted);">
      <li><a href="#philosophy" class="hover:text-navy transition-colors">Philosophy and Scope</a></li>
      <li><a href="#process" class="hover:text-navy transition-colors">The Admissions Process</a></li>
      <li><a href="#english" class="hover:text-navy transition-colors">English Language Requirements</a></li>
      <li><a href="#send" class="hover:text-navy transition-colors">SEND and Learning Needs</a></li>
      <li><a href="#financial" class="hover:text-navy transition-colors">Financial Obligations</a></li>
      <li><a href="#attendance" class="hover:text-navy transition-colors">Attendance and Conduct</a></li>
      <li><a href="#withdrawal" class="hover:text-navy transition-colors">Notice of Withdrawal</a></li>
      <li><a href="#contact" class="hover:text-navy transition-colors">Contacts</a></li>
    </ol>
  </nav>

  <div class="policy-body" style="font-size: 15px; font-family: var(--font-body); color: var(--color-charcoal); line-height: 1.75;">

    <h2 id="philosophy">1. Philosophy and Scope</h2>
    <p>ISJ seeks to admit pupils who will thrive academically, socially, and emotionally within the school community. Admissions are conducted without discrimination on the grounds of gender, race, nationality, religion, disability, or family background.</p>
    <p>This policy sets out the principles governing how places are allocated. The separate <a href="/admissions/terms-and-conditions" class="text-navy hover:text-navy/70 transition-colors underline underline-offset-2 decoration-charcoal/20">Admissions Terms and Conditions</a> govern the legal agreement between ISJ and each enrolled family once a place has been accepted.</p>

    <h2 id="process">2. The Admissions Process</h2>
    <p>Admission follows a structured sequence:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Submission of the official application form</li>
      <li>Provision of supporting documentation (previous school reports, medical information)</li>
      <li>Informal assessment, observation, or formal testing at ISJ's discretion</li>
      <li>A meeting between the family and the school</li>
      <li>Formal offer of a place, subject to availability</li>
      <li>Confirmation via signed Offer and Acceptance Letter and fee payment</li>
    </ol>
    <p>Decisions are based on the availability of places and ISJ's ability to meet the pupil's needs. Assessments are used to inform placement and support, not as a tool for academic selection.</p>

    <h2 id="english">3. English Language Requirements</h2>
    <p>As the language of instruction is English, applicants should have sufficient proficiency to access the curriculum. ISJ may admit a limited number of pupils with developing English where the school determines that appropriate progress can be made with available support. See also the <a href="/policies/eal" class="text-navy hover:text-navy/70 transition-colors underline underline-offset-2 decoration-charcoal/20">EAL Policy</a>.</p>

    <h2 id="send">4. SEND and Learning Needs</h2>
    <p>Families must disclose any known medical, psychological, or learning-related needs at the point of application and throughout the pupil's enrolment. ISJ will make reasonable adjustments within its existing resources. Where specialist services or significant additional resources are required, ISJ may charge separately or recommend external assessments. If a pupil's needs fall significantly outside the school's capacity to provide support, ISJ reserves the right to review or withdraw the placement. See also the <a href="/policies/send" class="text-navy hover:text-navy/70 transition-colors underline underline-offset-2 decoration-charcoal/20">SEND Policy</a>.</p>

    <h2 id="financial">5. Financial Obligations</h2>
    <p>All tuition, enrolment, capital contribution, and material fees must be paid in full as invoiced. Current fee amounts, payment schedules, late payment charges, and sanctions for non-payment are published on the <a href="/admissions/fees" class="text-navy hover:text-navy/70 transition-colors underline underline-offset-2 decoration-charcoal/20">fees page</a>, which forms an integral part of this agreement. Families experiencing financial difficulty should contact <a href="mailto:admissions@isj.id" class="text-navy hover:text-navy/70 transition-colors underline underline-offset-2 decoration-charcoal/20">admissions@isj.id</a> as early as possible.</p>

    <h2 id="attendance">6. Attendance and Conduct</h2>
    <p>Pupils are expected to attend regularly and adhere to the <a href="/admissions/behaviour-expectations" class="text-navy hover:text-navy/70 transition-colors underline underline-offset-2 decoration-charcoal/20">ISJ Behaviour Expectations</a>. Personal data is handled in accordance with the <a href="/privacy" class="text-navy hover:text-navy/70 transition-colors underline underline-offset-2 decoration-charcoal/20">Privacy Notice</a>. Pupils may be photographed or filmed for newsletters, marketing, or internal displays; parents wishing to limit this should notify admissions@isj.id in writing. In the event of circumstances beyond ISJ's control, the school may modify operations or move to remote learning while making reasonable efforts to continue educational provision.</p>

    <h2 id="withdrawal">7. Notice of Withdrawal</h2>
    <p>90 days' written notice is required to withdraw a pupil. Notice must be submitted to <a href="mailto:admissions@isj.id" class="text-navy hover:text-navy/70 transition-colors underline underline-offset-2 decoration-charcoal/20">admissions@isj.id</a> and takes effect only once acknowledged by the school. Where the required notice is not given, one full term's tuition fees will be charged in lieu.</p>

    <h2 id="contact">8. Contacts</h2>
    <div style="border-top: 1px solid rgba(26,42,68,0.08); margin-top: 1rem;">
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 0; font-size: 14px;">
        <div style="padding: 0.75rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(26,42,68,0.06); font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-navy);">Query type</div>
        <div style="padding: 0.75rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(26,42,68,0.06); font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-navy);">Contact</div>
        <div style="padding: 0.75rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(26,42,68,0.06);">Admissions, fees, withdrawals, complaints</div>
        <div style="padding: 0.75rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(26,42,68,0.06);"><a href="mailto:admissions@isj.id" class="text-navy hover:text-navy/70 transition-colors underline underline-offset-2 decoration-charcoal/20">admissions@isj.id</a></div>
        <div style="padding: 0.75rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(26,42,68,0.06);">General school information</div>
        <div style="padding: 0.75rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(26,42,68,0.06);"><a href="mailto:info@isj.id" class="text-navy hover:text-navy/70 transition-colors underline underline-offset-2 decoration-charcoal/20">info@isj.id</a></div>
        <div style="padding: 0.75rem 0;">Day-to-day academic matters</div>
        <div style="padding: 0.75rem 0;">Class teacher directly</div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

</PolicyLayout>
